-- Brazil sees eased requirements supporting loan growth guidance
-- By Luciana Otoni
-- Tue Jul 29, 2014 10:29AM EDT
-- None



BRASILIA, July 29 (Reuters) - Brazil central bank's decision last week to ease reserve requirements for certain credit segments will allow policymakers to support their estimate for a 12 percent expansion in bank lending this year, a central bank official said on Tuesday.   (Reporting by Luciana Otoni; Writing by Guillermo Parra-Bernal; Editing by James Dalgleish)  ((guillermo.parra@thomsonreuters.com)(+55-11-5644-7714)(+55-119 -8346-7153)(Reuters Messaging: guillermo.parra.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: BRAZIL ECONOMY/LENDING

